dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar run out (Samuels) 65 (102b 7x4 0x6 154m) SR: 63.72

dismissalComment.html: and it's another wicket in unfortunate circumstances! dismissalText.commentary: Harbhajan Singh c †Baugh b Gayle 37 (60b 1x4 2x6 56m) SR: 61.66

dismissalComment.html: wicket! Lands on a short length outside off, perhaps a little too close for that shot, he went for a square cut and got the thinnest of edges which Baugh did supremely well to snap, Harbhajan doesnt wait for the umpire's verdict and walks, his resistance ends and India are now seven down, Gayle gets a wicket to his name

headshotImage.caption: Rahul Dravid player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rahul Dravid player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: and he gets his man very early! The big wicket of Dravid! A beautiful delivery lands on off and moves the slightest bit, Dravid defends and the ball shaves the edge through to Carlton Baugh, a tame dismissal and West Indies have struck rich in just the first over, the ploy to begin with Smith's dobblers pays off

headshotImage.caption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: oh geez, he's struck twice! Wow! This pitches on a full length on off, moves in, Sehwag's feet go nowhere instead of forward, the ball just stays low and knocks back off stump, another tame dismissal but this was a man out of form, he has to go back and West Indies have knocked down two of India's big guns, well done Dwayne Smith!

dismissalComment.html: gone! A good ball, seam position worked, pitched outside off and Raina pokes at it, ball takes a thick outside edge and goes straight into Gayle's lap at slip, West Indies make further inroads

commentPostTextItems.html: Well, a low-scoring encounter turns out to be close. India have snuck in a good win to boost their morale and leave this tournament just that much more exciting as it means they need a win in the final league match on Friday. The West Indies, led by Dwayne Smith, bowled extremely well to bowl India out for 162, but in reply they turned in a bad effort in the face of a spirited Indian bowling attack.

So this is the deal: India must win on Friday, thats obvious, while Australia can get through with a tie or a wash-out. The West Indies have to yet again address their woeful middle and lower order batting when chasing. They have three days to do so before the final.
Harbhajan Singh has been awarded the Man-of-the-Match award for his crucial 37 and 3 for 35.
